---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="about" description="What factory floor is and why it exists.">
  <article class="mx-auto" style="max-width: 68ch;">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-8 mt-0">About</h1>
    <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none
                prose-p:font-serif prose-p:text-[var(--color-text)] prose-p:leading-relaxed
                prose-headings:font-sans prose-headings:font-semibold prose-headings:text-[var(--color-text)]
                prose-a:text-[var(--color-copper)] prose-a:no-underline hover:prose-a:underline">
      <p>
        <strong>factory floor</strong> is a build journal for <a href="https://github.com/adrianwedd/factory-floor">factory-floor</a> —
        a private CLI for 3D printing workflow. The pipeline runs from a <code>project.yaml</code>
        through parametric CAD, mesh validation, a slicer dry run, and a generated report.
        Nothing touches the printer without a human reading that report first.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site is the public record of building it: decisions made, things that failed,
        things that worked, and the reasoning behind the process.
      </p>
      <p>
        Built by <a href="https://adrianwedd.com">Adrian Wedd</a>, Tasmania.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
